7:
Hah...
It's finished... I'm finally finished!
11:
Good work today, Vice Commander
Keira. Sorry you had to stay so late.
15:
...There was plenty that would've
been finished much sooner if you
had done it instead...
19:
Hey, now. I've got my hands full too.
You know those higher-ups can't
change their diapers all by
themselves.
21:
Look. This is their brand-new plan for
where to station the Guild Knights in
the event of a disaster.
25:
...This is absurd. Do they really
believe no Purgers will appear
outside the walls or in Shibuya?
29:
I doubt they even believe in those
things to begin with. Either way, we
are understaffed.
33:
We can get help from Starview
Village, can we not? Surely we can
do better than this!
37:
Yeah, and why stop there? We could
just keep going until we're a
completely unstoppable military
force.
40:
If you intend to "use" those people...
Well, it might not be a bad idea. I'm
sure some of our superiors would be
thrilled.
44:
...I just want us to do what we can to
protect the people.
46:
I don't want the Guild Knights to
become too big, either. Even the
commander—
50:
Think about this, Vice Commander.
You can't put everything on Finn.
58:
We've gotta handle this ourselves,
right?
61:
I'll put in a request to have them
reconsider this plan of theirs. If
you've got a better plan, let me
know.
67: "A better plan," he says so casually...
71:
Captain Zekhel, pardon me! I was
hoping you could check these
documents for me today!
74:
Sorry, he just left.
...Or, rather, he ran away. Again.
78:
It's not fair! Your unit is always
getting all the captain's attention!
Just look at all the documents we've
been waiting for him to check!
81:
Wh-what? It's not like he's paying us
any attention either. I mean, he just
ran away from me again—
84:
We're in huge trouble with
Halloween coming up! Now that the
main street's been cleared, there's
talk of a festival being held in
Shibuya!
86:
I heard that Halloween in Shibuya
gets extremely crowded, so I have
no idea how we're going to handle
this!
90:
All right! I'll handle the logistics for
Halloween! I'll even send out security
from our unit to help! Is that good
enough?!
93:
Th-thank you very much! W-we'll let
you know about the costume and
other details as soon as we can!
96:
...Well, at least I'm used to guard
duty. If that's where my extra tasks
end, I should be fine—
118:
Thanks. Really. You've more than
made your point.
121:
Tch... That Addie. I said I'd be fine
with a more reserved outfit...
126:
It should be all right. Surely the Guild
wanted the security team to fit in
with the crowd, no?
129:
That's right, Vice Commander.
Besides, dressed like this, perhaps
you'll catch a compliment from the
commander.
132:
...Heh. Don't think you can tease me
like this forever.
135:
The commander is busy. He doesn't
have time to participate—
147:
I heard about the security situation,
but if you're there, I'm sure it'll be
fine. I'm heading out to investigate.
158:
I see.
It looks great on you.
167:
Did you notice that weird pause? It'd
be so much easier if you just
confessed to him already.
171:
To your stations! Hurry! Take your
positions! Go, go!
174:
Stella, please. Whatever you're
about to say, don't.
177: I'm past my limit. I'm gonna die.
186:
Anyway! First and foremost, there's
work to be done! Shibuya is
supposed to get really crowded and
rowdy on Halloween.
189:
Stella. I need your help to make it
through this!
193:
Please don't push! Keep moving and
keep the path clear—
195:
No, YOU apologize! You're the one
who pushed me!
203:
We're the Guild Knights—the officers
entrusted with your safety.
205:
If anything's making you angry or
uneasy, blame it all on the Guild
Knights tonight. Those things don't
have any place at a fun festival.
208:
We have just one request. Please
create a little space in front of you
to allow others to walk by.
211:
If you'd like to receive a gift, please
visit the Guild Knights. The password
is "trick or treat!"
215:
Thanks for your help, Stella. Please
return to your post now.
226:
...What is it that I want to protect?
Well, that's an easy question to
answer.
231:
But what will I do?
I'll have to answer that question
sooner than later.
